I&#x27;m skeptical about the way state can change from under you within the same execution of the rendering function. This type of mutability will prevent all the help that typescript normally gives for complex components.<p>Also if anyone has used it, do you have to use this pattern if you have derived state?<p><pre><code>    setState({
      displayName: `${state.user.firstName} ${state.user.lastName}`
    })
</code></pre>
If you simply do `const displayName = ...` in the component, will the component update properly?
